FT  16 APR 91 / UK Company News: Southern Water in Pounds 55m loan facility
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Southern Water has arranged a Pounds 55m loan facility with the European
Investment Bank, the second and final tranche of a Pounds 95m funding
programme agreed in September last year.
The 15-year facility will be used to finance Southern's capital expenditure
programme, which currently absorbs around Pounds 3m a week. Many of the
projects being funded are required under UK and European Community
legislation.
The interest rate will not be fixed until the funds are drawn down by
Southern. The company pays a fixed 11 per cent interest on the initial
Pounds 40m loan arranged last year.
In common with many other UK water companies, Southern has opted to finance
capital expenditure through the EIB rather than borrow from the capital
markets in it's own name.
