<HEADLINE>
FT  15 APR 91 / Construction Contracts: Contracts worth Pounds 3.7m won by
Don Reynolds
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
DON REYNOLDS, the curtain walling subsidiary of Henry Barrett Group, has
been awarded contracts worth about Pounds 3.7m. The four contracts, two in
Scotland, one in Northern Ireland and one in England, will use Series 200,
400 and 500 of the curtain waIling systems.
A four-storey extension plus refurbishment to the Amerada Hess building in
Aberdeen will be carried out by Don Reynolds. It will be the Hess
Corporation's new European headquarters. The project is worth about Pounds
1.2m and the main contractor is Miller Construction, also from Edinburgh.
The curtain wallers will build a four-storey office block for Scottish
Nuclear Fuels' headquarters in East Kilbride. The main contractor is the GA
Group and the project value is about Pounds 1.1m.
After the IRA firebombing on January 5 of Sprucefields Shopping Centre in
Lisburn, Northern Ireland, Don Reynolds will rebuild the single-storey
units. The main contractors are McLaughlin and Harvey, Belfast, and the
contract value is about Pounds 950,000.
Glenlivet Properties has awarded a contract for a three-storey office
development at Carbrook Hall, Sheffield. The main contractors are Bowmer and
Kirkland and the contract is worth about Pounds 450,000.
