<HEADLINE>
FT  15 APR 91 / Construction Contracts: Offices plan in Salford
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
MANCHESTER-based Co-operative Bank has awarded WIMPEY CONSTRUCTION NORTH
WEST a Pounds 1.2m contract to extend its facilities at Montford Street, in
the heart of the Salford enterprise zone.
Over seven months, Wimpey will design and build 12,000 sq ft of additional
office space for the administration centre, which serves the bank's
north-west operation.
Architect Austin Strzala Turner, in conjunction with White Young Consulting
Engineers, has produced a design for the two-storey extension to complement
the original building, put up by Wimpey three years ago.
The Co-operative Property Group is acting as employer's agent for the
scheme.
MOWLEM EUROPE, in joint venture with Conran Roche, is to undertake an
economic and infrastructure study for the Schwedt/Angermunde region of
eastern Germany. Work will last throughout this year.
