<TEXT>
Sir, I think it is perverse for you to say that road-pricing is the least of
all evils. As you rightly point out, at present motorists pay only a
fraction of the cost that society incurs because of their action.
Road-pricing would help restore the rightful balance. It is therefore a good
thing.
Following your logic, would the 55p price of the Financial Times also be an
evil?
